Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "radujem" in different forms and positions:

1. *Radujem* se tvojoj novoj knjizi. (I am looking forward to your new book.)
2. Nadam se da se *raduješ* mom dolasku. (I hope you're excited about my arrival.)
3. *Raduje* me što smo se opet videli. (I'm happy that we've seen each other again.)
4. *Radovao sam se* letovanju, ali se vreme pokvarilo. (I was looking forward to the vacation, but the weather turned bad.)
5. *Raduje me* tvoj uspeh na fakultetu. (I'm happy about your success in college.)
6. Kada se *raduješ*, cela soba blista. (When you're happy, the whole room lights up.)
7. *Radujem* se izazovima koje život donosi. (I embrace the challenges that life brings.)

In each sentence, the word "radujem" is either conjugated differently or used in a different position within the sentence. The translations in English are provided in parentheses after each sentence.